Reception given to mark KPA birthday 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- The Ministry of the People's Armed Forces hosted a reception on Tuesday to mark the 69th birthday of the heroic Korean People's Army.
 Invited to the reception were military attaches of foreign embassies here.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Vice-minister of the People's Armed Forces Ryo Chun Sok and generals and officers of the KPA were present. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there.

Polish charge d'affaires calls press conference 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Mieczyslaw Dedo, charge d'affaires ad interim of the Polish embassy here, called a press conference at the Taedonggang Club for the diplomatic corps on Tuesday on the occasion of the National Day of Poland.
 Present there were mediapersons in the city of Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the conference the charge d'affaires referred to the significance of the constitution instituted in Poland on May 3, 1791, adding that this day is observed as national day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He also mentioned the matter of developing the friendly relations between Poland and the DPRK.

DPRK photo exhibition opens to mark KPA birthday 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- A DPRK photo exhibition opened in Russia on April 13 on the occasion of the 69th anniversary of the heroic Korean People's Army. 
 Displayed at the exhibition were photos showing exploits performed by president Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il for the strengthening and development of the revolutionary armed forces of the DPRK and the invincible might of the KPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At an inaugural ceremony speakers said that the exhibition would offer an opportunity to know better about the great idea, leadership and noble traits of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, expressing belief that the exhibition would have a good impact on Russian people from all walks of life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants saw the Korean film "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Jong Il Meets With President Of The Russian Federation Putin."

Words of songs praising Kim Jong Il created in South Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Many words of songs have been created and widely disseminated among South Koreans on the occasion of Sun's Day, Seoul-based radio Voice of National Salvation reported. These words express reverence for leader Kim Jong Il.
 Among them are "We live near the general", "Songi mushrooms on Mt. Chilbo", "Swallow here for reunification" and "We are proud of being the nation of the sun". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The words said that the footsteps taken by Kim Jong Il with loving care for the people lead to all parts of South Korea and South Koreans, therefore, live near him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Songi mushrooms on Mt. Chilbo sent by Kim Jong Il represent his ardent love for the same nation and the same fellow countrymen, the words noted, saying that these mushrooms have become the greatest speciality in the world under his care. Even the Koreans who live in an alien land far away from the homeland live trusting Kim Jong Il only, the words said, adding they are proud of being the nation of the sun.

U.S.-S. Korea joint military exercise under fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Liewelyn John, leader of the People's Democratic Movement of Guyana, in a statement issued on April 17 demanded the U.S. immediately halt the reckless war exercise on the Korean peninsula and withdraw its troops from South Korea, a main obstacle to Korean reunification.
 Noting that the U.S. and South Korean authorities are staging "reception, staging, onward movement and integration" (RSOI) exercise, challenging the aspirations and ardent desire of the peace-loving people of the world and the entire Korean nation for reunification, the statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This shows that the U.S. is chiefly responsible for the strained international situation and the chieftain of aggression and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The purpose of this war exercise now under way under the simulated conditions of an actual war is to annul the DPRK-U.S. agreed framework which calls for refraining from threatening the dialogue partner by force of arms and isolate and stifle the DPRK at any cost. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement termed the war exercise an undisguised aggressive move against the DPRK and bitterly denounced it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Samuel Walker, chairman of the Guyana Labour Union, in a statement issued on April 18 denounced the U.S. and South Korea for their "RSOI" exercise, noting that the U.S. anti-DPRK war moves have created serious difficulties in the way of implementing the north-south joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the South Korean authorities let their army take part in the war exercise, cooperating with the U.S. in its anti-DPRK war moves, they will strongly be protested and denounced by the peace-loving people of the world for their undisguised perfidy to the north-south joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will firmly stand by the Korean people who love justice and peace and extend full support and solidarity to the Korean people in their just struggle to defend the dignity and sovereignty of the country.

Japan-DPRK friendship organization inaugurated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- The Dietmen's League for the Promotion of Japan-Korea Friendship of the Marco Society for Justice was inaugurated in Japan on March 21. 
 The league is aimed to promote the friendship and mutual interests between Japan and the DPRK and boost exchange in different fields to establish diplomatic relations between them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the inaugural ceremony the league discussed the issue of organizing  colorful solidarity activities in the "period of the international solidarity movement to bring earlier the independent reunification of Korea." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An appeal adopted at the ceremony expressed the expectation that through talks for the establishment of diplomatic relations between the two countries Japan would liquidate the history of the past war and colonial rule over Korea and friendship and understanding not only between the two governments but between non-governmental organizations of the two countries would be deepened. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The appeal urged the government to establish diplomatic relations with the DPRK at an early date in the 21st century so that Japan and the DPRK may be near and close countries, not near yet distant ones.

Anniversary of KPA observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Papers here today editorially observe the 69th anniversary of the heroic Korean People's Army.
 Rodong Sinmun in an editorial captioned "Let's emerge ever-victorious under the banner of the great army-first idea" says that 70-odd-year history of the heroic KPA is a proud  history in which it has defended the revolutionary cause of Juche, winning victory after victory under the army-first banner held aloft by the generals of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The editorial continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The distinguished personality of President Kim Il Sung as a great man and his exploits lie in that he founded the army before anything else guided by the army-first idea and opened a new road of advancing the revolution with the army as its main force. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The path covered by the Korean revolutionary armed forces since the first gun report in the forest of Mt. Paektu represents the glorious history in which they have fought as the vanguard of the generals of Mt. Paektu, learning from the idea, will, traits and spirit of general Kim Il Sung, commander of guerrillas on Mt. Paektu who founded and led the KPA, general Kim Jong Suk, anti-Japanese heroine, and general Kim Jong Il, supreme commander of the KPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The editorial makes a particular mention about the fact that Kim Jong Il created the mode of army-first politics in the arduous period in which the country was at the crossroads: Defending  socialism or becoming a slave of imperialism and has solved all the problems arising in the revolution and construction in reliance upon the powerful KPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA is a strong army based on comradeship whose servicepersons are firmly united thanks to the army-first idea and will of Kim Jong Il and an invincible army which always emerges victorious as Kim Jong Il does. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army-first banner of the Workers' Party of Korea is the banner of victory of Korean-style socialism which made the red flag of revolution vigorously flutter in this land and an everlasting banner of struggle which should always be held aloft as long as imperialism exists on the earth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il is the great successor to the lineage of Mt. Paektu and the tradition of army-first revolution and a staunch defender of socialism who emerges ever-victorious in the confrontation with imperialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people's army and the people of Korea will glorify the exploits Kim Il Sung performed in the army building for all ages, guided by the army-first idea of Kim Jong Il and under his leadership, and accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche to completion with the might of the invincible army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson carries an editorial titled "The Korean people's army will demonstrate its honour of being the main force to accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche."

Evening gala of servicemen held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- An evening gala of the Ministry of the  People's Armed Forces was held in Jonsung Square yesterday on the occasion of the 69th anniversary of the heroic Korean People's Army (KPA).
 The stage in the square was decorated with letters "Celebration of April 25." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Jo Myong Rok, director of the general political department of the KPA, Kim Yong Chun, chief of the KPA general staff, Kim Il Chol, minister of the people's armed forces, generals, officers and men of the KPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its participants had a variety of dances to the tune of the songs "Glory to the Dear Leader Kim Jong Il," "Song of Three Prides," etc. They extended highest glory and warmest congratulations to supreme commander Kim Jong Il who has led the Korean revolution to victory by strengthening and developing the KPA to be an invincible army with his great army-first politics and putting forward it as a main force in the revolution.

Youth and students meet with DPRK heroes and heroine 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, April 25 (KCNA) -- Youth and students met with DPRK heroes and heroine at the Central Youth Hall yesterday on the occasion of the 69th anniversary of the heroic Korean People's Army.
 Hero of the Republic Ryom Thae Gyong, lecturer at the victorious Fatherland Liberation War Museum, said that the soldiers of the people's army heroically fought all the battles including the battle on Height 1211 during the past Fatherland Liberation War and expressed the belief that the youth and students would glorify their youth in the sacred struggle to defend the headquarters of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Young hero and heroine of the Republic Jong Kwang Son and Jong Song Ok said that they demonstrated the dignity and honour of Juche Korea with iron will and stamina and renewed their determination to devote themselves to the drive to build a powerful prosperous nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Youth and students also took the floor to evince their resolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, an oratorical meeting of agricultural workers on the subject "Long live the great army-first politics " was held on April 23 on the same occasion.
